<!-- Start Body -->

In the past i've taken Adderall and wellbutrin, but never mixed them. Wellbutrin never did anything to me, no anti-depressent ever did.  One day at school a friend of mine gave me 60mg of Wellbutrin and 30mg of Adderall, me being stupid not knowing about either of these drugs, mixed them.<BR>
<BR>
The effects were horrible, for the first 2 hours i felt great, everything felt really good, like a pleasurable ache in my whole body, its hard to explain but it was a good feeling.  Soon after that the effects were horrible. i kept shivering, almost passed out and had the worst stomach ache ever.  The shiverness sorta thing lasted for about 3 days and i was up straight for 2.  If you ever have the chance to mix these, i recomend you don't.<!-- End Body -->
<br/><br style="clear:both;"/>


